<style>
  /* Isolate test variants — each gets its own wrapper class so I can
     toggle one variable at a time without cross-contamination. */
  .dag-test-page { max-width: 720px; margin: 2rem auto; padding: 0 1rem; }
  .dag-test-page h1 { font-family: var(--type-serif); margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .dag-test-page p.intro { font-family: var(--type-mono); font-size: 13px; opacity: 0.8; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .dag-test-variant { margin-bottom: 2.5rem; padding: 1rem; border: 1px solid var(--nib); border-radius: 4px; }
  .dag-test-variant h2 {
    font-family: var(--type-mono); font-size: 13px; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem; color: var(--nib);
  }
  .dag-test-variant .hypothesis {
    font-family: var(--type-mono); font-size: 11px; opacity: 0.7; margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .dag-test-variant svg { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
  .dag-test-variant text { font-family: var(--type-mono); font-size: 9px; fill: var(--ink); }
  .dag-test-variant .node-label { font-size: 10px; }
  .dag-test-variant .node-label-sm { font-size: 8.5px; }

  /* V1 (control): reuse existing .dag-schematic CSS — no changes here. */

  /* V2 (all 70×30 rects): same CSS as control. */

  /* V3 (crispEdges): same CSS. The attribute is on each rect. */

  /* V4 (no fade-in groups): defeat the fade-in rules for this variant. */
  .dag-test-noanim rect { opacity: 1 !important; }

  /* V5 (always opacity 1): override fade-in CSS. */
  .dag-test-always-visible .fade-in { opacity: 1 !important; }

  /* V6 (no markers): no marker-end on paths. Same rect CSS. */

  /* V7 (all attributes, no CSS): deliberately no CSS class match.
     Stroke/stroke-width/fill all live on rect as attributes. */
  .dag-test-attrs-only rect { stroke: none; fill: inherit; }

  /* V8 (SVG-internal <style>): CSS lives inside the SVG. */

  /* V9 (smaller rendered size): cap width. */
  .dag-test-small { max-width: 320px; }

  /* V10 (fill-opacity="1" explicit): rect has fill-opacity="1" attribute. */

  /* V11: stroke="none" — remove stroke entirely, see if the stroke cascade is interfering */
  .dag-test-no-stroke rect { stroke: none !important; }

  /* V12: <img> embedded SVG (test if inline vs external differs) */
  .dag-test-img img { width: 100%; display: block; }
</style>

<div class="dag-test-page">
  <h1>DAG paint diagnostic</h1>
  <p class="intro">
    Twelve variants of the DAG, each toggling one thing. On Firefox Android,
    soft-reload the page and tell me the variant numbers where the lower-tier
    rects render <strong>dark</strong> (correct) vs <strong>white/cream</strong>
    (the bug). That narrows it to one variable.
  </p>

